The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, June 16: The rate of inflation rose to 4.72 per cent during the week ended June 3, against 4.68 per cent in the previous week, due to higher prices of fruits, vegetables and some manufactured products. The rate stood at 4.39 per cent during the corresponding week of the previous year. The official data on inflation released today did not factor in the increase in prices of petrol and diesel announced on June 5. 

 Chennai, June 16: Tata Consultancy Services plans to hire about 30,000 people this year across the globe, said S. Padmanaban, executive vice-president and head-global human resources at TCS. The company proposes to recruit 7,500 people in Tamil Nadu this year, he added.

 New Delhi, June 16: The government is likely to issue the first tranche of bonds worth Rs 7,000 crore to oil marketing companies next week. The bonds are part of a package to help companies offset their under recoveries due to surging international prices of petroleum.

 Mumbai, June 16: Glenmark Pharmaceuticals? subsidiary Bouwer-Bartlett has acquired seven products from South Africa-based PD Pharmaceuticals for an undisclosed amount.

 Mumbai, June 16: The Shipping Corporation of India (SCI) has applied to the government for permission to recruit foreign crewmen for short-term durations.




